I really don't understand how.

01:02:20.120 --> 01:02:21.354
Oh, it's very helpful.

01:02:22.120 --> 01:02:23.920
Maybe a neighbor is tossing his leaf clippings on your lawn

01:02:24.403 --> 01:02:25.293
or looking at your woman

01:02:26.120 --> 01:02:27.617
or harboring desires regarding your longboat.

01:02:27.920 --> 01:02:30.257
You enslave his children, set his house on fire.

01:02:30.940 --> 01:02:32.578
He shall not bother you again.

01:02:32.940 --> 01:02:34.720
It must be nice to have you as a neighbor, not...

01:02:34.920 --> 01:02:37.337
I live in no place longer than needed to fulfill my goals,

01:02:37.920 --> 01:02:39.295
taking slaves, valuables, and food.

01:02:39.920 --> 01:02:42.297
Goal setting is very important, Amy, not just in football.

01:02:42.920 --> 01:02:44.599
You're very weird and creeping me out a bit,

01:02:44.920 --> 01:02:47.297
but whatever, no weirder than anything else.

01:02:48.021 --> 01:02:49.720
So, what do you think of my city?

01:02:50.163 --> 01:02:51.578
Ah, I like it very much.

01:02:51.981 --> 01:02:53.720
Your women here are prepared for battle.

01:02:54.141 --> 01:02:57.117
They are large, not like those scrawny things to the north.

01:02:57.720 --> 01:03:00.097
A woman who wheats well provides for her man.

01:03:00.720 --> 01:03:03.278
You cannot set sail for robbing and pillaging on an empty stomach.

01:03:03.720 --> 01:03:05.916
It's like the story of the parson's wife and the troll.

01:03:06.760 --> 01:03:08.520
I don't think I've ever heard of that one.

01:03:08.720 --> 01:03:11.520
Great Carl Erson, ye mainlanders have no historical perspective.

01:03:12.003 --> 01:03:12.832
Read the runes.

01:03:13.781 --> 01:03:14.387
It's all right there.

01:03:14.408 --> 01:03:15.520
Talk to a grandparent.

01:03:15.942 --> 01:03:18.298
But no, ye cast people out like rubbish.

01:03:18.720 --> 01:03:20.459
Wisdom is not to be treated so lightly.

01:03:20.942 --> 01:03:23.198
When my father grew old, I sat with him day and night,

01:03:23.720 --> 01:03:25.520
absorbing his wisdom, learning about the demons

01:03:25.841 --> 01:03:27.500
and where the wickedness resides in men's hearts.

01:03:28.062 --> 01:03:30.359
Then as his time grew near, I built a large pyre,

01:03:30.720 --> 01:03:32.520
burnt him and his wife while communing with Odin's spirit.

01:03:33.224 --> 01:03:35.520
Careful, Musty Pines is a sponsor of the show.

01:03:36.023 --> 01:03:37.459
Oh, Grody, what are you doing?

01:03:37.720 --> 01:03:39.399
I'm just adjusting myself, she-devil.

01:03:39.720 --> 01:03:41.459
Wearing these animal hides does get a bit itchy.

01:03:42.064 --> 01:03:43.176
Um, okay.

01:03:43.720 --> 01:03:44.788
You never answered my question.

01:03:45.029 --> 01:03:46.419
What do you think of Vice City?

01:03:47.163 --> 01:03:49.520
Your land and people have a lot in common with mine.

01:03:49.720 --> 01:03:51.520
You see, we too fled our homes due to lack of food,

01:03:51.720 --> 01:03:53.014
overpopulation and the bitter cold.

01:03:54.585 --> 01:03:57.500
And, mind ye, darting out to raid passing ships is fine,

01:03:57.740 --> 01:03:59.520
but we needed a new land to have our way with.

01:04:00.163 --> 01:04:02.500
Granted, we roll and sail to an area, land in force

01:04:02.720 --> 01:04:04.520
and burn down a local monastery or village,

01:04:05.003 --> 01:04:06.500
whereas you come in, destroy all the creatures,

01:04:07.286 --> 01:04:08.520
and sell plastic versions of them.

01:04:09.145 --> 01:04:10.520
You did a fine job pillaging these lands,

01:04:11.365 --> 01:04:13.520
but ye should have done something about Canada.

01:04:13.861 --> 01:04:15.573
Wait a minute there, Buster.

01:04:15.593 --> 01:04:16.439
My mother's half Canadian.

01:04:16.720 --> 01:04:18.500
Oh, what are you going to do, wench?

01:04:19.404 --> 01:04:21.153
Sweep the ice furiously at me?

01:04:21.394 --> 01:04:21.555
Ha!

01:04:21.957 --> 01:04:22.520
Socialize medicine?

01:04:22.922 --> 01:04:24.500
Nay, you did it all wrong.

01:04:25.083 --> 01:04:27.460
You should have continued to the north and finished things off.

01:04:28.022 --> 01:04:30.419
I talk about this in me motivational learning tapes.

01:04:30.720 --> 01:04:32.277
That, and beware the magpie.

01:04:32.740 --> 01:04:33.324
Tis the devil.

01:04:33.848 --> 01:04:35.258
Evil reigneth when darkness falls.

01:04:35.861 --> 01:04:36.506
Are you married?

01:04:36.667 --> 01:04:38.439
You seem like a tough character to live with.

01:04:38.740 --> 01:04:39.751
Aye, me wife Helga.

01:04:40.055 --> 01:04:40.520
What a hag!

01:04:41.062 --> 01:04:44.520
This show is not sexist, whatever certain bearded women might say.

01:04:44.841 --> 01:04:45.969
Women are people too.

01:04:46.291 --> 01:04:47.016
I'd appreciate...

01:04:48.165 --> 01:04:49.520
Go live in a chimney, ye troll.

01:04:50.023 --> 01:04:51.520
You twentieth century women are all the same.

01:04:52.385 --> 01:04:54.520
And me hag Helga, she fell prey to your uppity ways.

01:04:54.720 --> 01:04:55.335
She says to me,

01:04:55.720 --> 01:04:55.864
Thar,

01:04:56.520 --> 01:04:58.732
Thar, I ain't havin' no mead no more.

01:04:58.993 --> 01:04:59.998
I'm goin' to meetings.

01:05:00.540 --> 01:05:00.844
See?

01:05:01.187 --> 01:05:02.057
That's your problem.

01:05:02.520 --> 01:05:05.280
Soon as you sort something out, you have to go preaching from the rooftops

01:05:05.841 --> 01:05:10.320
to everyone else how to live, not pillage nor plunder no more, but live in boxes.

01:05:10.705 --> 01:05:11.320
Then she says,

01:05:11.661 --> 01:05:16.039
Thar, I'm getting me stomach stapled, I look fat, and now fit as two yakskins,

01:05:16.520 --> 01:05:17.855
where previously t'was only one.

01:05:18.520 --> 01:05:22.300
I say, wench, don't come cryin' to me when we're in a longboat crossing the straits for two moons,

01:05:22.520 --> 01:05:23.789
and you're all skin and bones.

01:05:24.212 --> 01:05:25.320
A man needs somethin' to grab onto.

01:05:25.983 --> 01:05:27.029
I ain't her fault.

01:05:27.411 --> 01:05:28.999
A cursed pixie goblin got her.

01:05:29.320 --> 01:05:30.245
Pixie goblin?

01:05:30.305 --> 01:05:33.100
What kind of weird ancient nonsense are you talking about?

01:05:33.642 --> 01:05:36.959
Now, Thar, I've got to ask you, how old are you?

01:05:37.602 --> 01:05:40.120
I am as old as a fjord's, as young as a newborn lamb.

01:05:41.144 --> 01:05:42.632
Are you shy about your age?

01:05:42.652 --> 01:05:43.798
Just lie about it, like my mom.

01:05:44.602 --> 01:05:45.649
Thar is never shy.

01:05:45.690 --> 01:05:46.395
Thar is mighty.

01:05:46.435 --> 01:05:47.120
Thar is a god.

01:05:47.846 --> 01:05:48.857
And where are you from?

01:05:49.320 --> 01:05:51.858
From the beginning of the flat earth, where the sun meets the sky.

01:05:52.340 --> 01:05:52.967
Oh, right.

01:05:53.028 --> 01:05:53.574
By the beach.

01:05:53.736 --> 01:05:54.059
Great.

01:05:54.321 --> 01:05:55.389
Let's take a commercial break.

01:05:55.409 --> 01:05:56.779
We'll be right back with Thar.

01:05:57.120 --> 01:05:58.151
He's a real viking.

01:05:58.192 --> 01:05:58.900
Yeah, right, whatever.

01:05:59.221 --> 01:06:00.920
Hello, I am Fernando Martinez.

01:06:01.462 --> 01:06:03.920
I think by now you know I am an emotional kind of guy.

01:06:04.824 --> 01:06:07.920
People stop me in the street and say, Fernando, what the hell is wrong with me?

01:06:08.662 --> 01:06:12.679
Silk shirt, hairy chest, enough aftershave to drown a household pet.

01:06:13.120 --> 01:06:14.900
But I still cannot get a woman.

01:06:15.363 --> 01:06:16.677
I tell them you are an ignorant fool.

01:06:17.704 --> 01:06:19.920
Without a symbol of power and fertility around your neck,

01:06:20.785 --> 01:06:22.860
what kind of woman is going to respect you?

01:06:23.784 --> 01:06:27.700
That is why I have teamed up with Medallion Man, the shop for medallion needs.

01:06:28.424 --> 01:06:30.720
Medallion Man caters to all levels of masculinity.

01:06:31.301 --> 01:06:36.720
For the strong silent type, a medallion the size of a hubcap will say everything that needs to be said.

01:06:37.543 --> 01:06:41.660
Even singing medallions for the Casanova, who knows music, is the food of love.

01:06:42.562 --> 01:06:47.680
Model trains, dollhouses, diapers, whatever is your interest, we've got the medallion for you.

01:06:47.980 --> 01:06:52.720
Don't forget, every woman knows, if you can't support a medallion, you can't support me.

01:06:52.920 --> 01:06:57.097
Don't worry family, we have some sad news for you.

01:06:58.081 --> 01:07:00.735
Rock and roll is dead and pop is in.

01:07:01.980 --> 01:07:07.359
Why not discover the excitement of the science of music yourself at Synth & Son, the home of keyboards.

01:07:07.960 --> 01:07:12.379
Thanks to the science of music, you don't need musical talent to make great music, just listen.

01:07:13.524 --> 01:07:15.337
I created that just by pressing a button.

01:07:15.960 --> 01:07:17.700
Synthesizers are the new wave.

01:07:18.161 --> 01:07:22.519
Why work hard on difficult compositions when a machine can make music better than you've ever dreamed of?

01:07:23.001 --> 01:07:24.417
You'll be the hit of the party.

01:07:24.920 --> 01:07:28.579
It's perfect for in-restaurant entertainment, cover bands and funerals.

01:07:28.920 --> 01:07:31.519
Make fugues funky and death marches danceable.

01:07:31.940 --> 01:07:34.116
It's the science of music at Synth & Son.

01:07:34.920 --> 01:07:37.654
Remember, you don't know you're a musician until you try.

01:07:41.261 --> 01:07:47.319
We're back on KChat with me, Amy, and my guest is Thor, Viking warrior and elf help guru.

01:07:47.920 --> 01:07:48.830
Do you have a last name?

01:07:48.850 --> 01:07:49.316
Oh, whatever.

01:07:49.920 --> 01:07:51.316
Anyway, what were we talking about?

01:07:51.862 --> 01:07:53.520
We were talking about the wisdom of the ancients.

01:07:54.145 --> 01:07:55.520
There are many hurdles in life, Amy.

01:07:55.983 --> 01:07:57.480
I remember one of the first bits of fan mail I got.

01:07:57.801 --> 01:07:58.893
It came by bottle in the sea.

01:07:59.862 --> 01:08:01.520
A man of Lollard Island said,

01:08:01.901 --> 01:08:04.500
A tiny woman came to our farm and swept in front of our door.

01:08:04.982 --> 01:08:07.298
A woodland troll has carried off my woman in the dead of night.

01:08:07.720 --> 01:08:08.520
Give me wisdom, Thor!

01:08:08.862 --> 01:08:10.399
So, what did you tell him?

01:08:10.881 --> 01:08:11.344
Hi, Amy.

01:08:11.425 --> 01:08:13.500
It was obvious the Black Plague had visited his home.

01:08:13.961 --> 01:08:19.520
As sure as you can't be a midwife to a fairy, expect wisdom from a fool or find a good meal downtown on a Saturday night.

01:08:20.347 --> 01:08:21.116
Okay.

01:08:21.781 --> 01:08:26.059
I don't, um, I really have nothing to ask you because I really don't think we're bonding quite right here.

01:08:26.540 --> 01:08:27.814
I'm more than a little confused.

01:08:28.520 --> 01:08:29.386
Let's go to the phones.

01:08:29.688 --> 01:08:31.098
You're on KChat with Thor.

01:08:31.520 --> 01:08:32.245
Yes, hello, Thor.

01:08:32.285 --> 01:08:33.071
My name's Jay.

01:08:33.152 --> 01:08:34.280
I'm a huge fan, man.

01:08:34.943 --> 01:08:37.139
Your book really helped me get through puberty.

01:08:37.580 --> 01:08:39.850
Everyone else was into vampires and stuff.

01:08:40.111 --> 01:08:41.497
I just got into the Viking thing.

01:08:41.517 --> 01:08:42.300
It's pretty cool.

01:08:42.641 --> 01:08:44.280
It's been working pretty well for me.

01:08:44.560 --> 01:08:47.018
Anyway, my girlfriend and I, we fight all the time.

01:08:47.520 --> 01:08:49.259
She's always calling to check up on me.

01:08:49.621 --> 01:08:50.875
It really totally sucks.

01:08:51.320 --> 01:08:51.822
It's a drag.

01:08:52.063 --> 01:08:55.638
Like, I hang out at the strip mall with all my boys, and she shows up.

01:08:56.320 --> 01:08:57.291
Is there any advice you can give me?

01:08:58.340 --> 01:08:58.641
Ah, yes.

01:08:59.223 --> 01:09:03.598
There was a man who asked for a night's lodging at a certain farm on the eve of Maundy Thursday.

01:09:04.320 --> 01:09:05.210
Or maybe it was Fat Tuesday.

01:09:06.320 --> 01:09:11.036
Anyway, in the course of the night, the old woman of the house took out a horn of salve and smeared herself with it from head to toe.

01:09:12.320 --> 01:09:15.919
She then climbed on top of the stove, sat astride a sweeping broom, and began to...

01:09:16.320 --> 01:09:16.542
Um, hello?

01:09:16.562 --> 01:09:18.375
Excuse me, what the hell are you talking about?

01:09:19.120 --> 01:09:19.909
It's a man's rune, wench.

01:09:21.282 --> 01:09:22.414
What kind of rune is that?

01:09:23.120 --> 01:09:25.497
Aye, it's a man's rune, and not appropriate for the warrior under 18 years old.

01:09:26.120 --> 01:09:26.966
But there's a moral at the end.

01:09:27.208 --> 01:09:28.316
Are you still there, Fair J?

01:09:29.120 --> 01:09:29.747
Uh, yeah, I'm still here.

01:09:31.181 --> 01:09:32.778
Do you love this woman?

01:09:33.120 --> 01:09:33.562
Yeah, I think so.

01:09:33.622 --> 01:09:34.526
She's really special.

01:09:34.546 --> 01:09:37.458
Especially in the back seat, if you know what I mean, Thor.

01:09:38.120 --> 01:09:41.779
Then behead her, and parade thy love around on a stick for the world to admire.

01:09:42.262 --> 01:09:42.909
Wow, cool.

01:09:43.030 --> 01:09:43.738
Thanks, Thor.

01:09:44.401 --> 01:09:47.779
Okay, I'd like to throw you out, but you've got an enormous sword,

01:09:47.940 --> 01:09:50.639
and, uh, yeah, let's take another call.

01:09:51.000 --> 01:09:55.660
But first, listeners, Vice City, remember, don't behead your girlfriend and take her head around on a stick.

01:09:55.940 --> 01:09:57.720
Hello, you're on KChat with Thor.

01:09:58.442 --> 01:10:00.350
Hey, brother, my name is T.J.

01:10:00.591 --> 01:10:02.720
Your book is fresh, real fresh.

01:10:03.424 --> 01:10:05.559
Like, it's been a real inspiration and all that.

01:10:05.920 --> 01:10:11.399
It's most definitely on me and my crew's vibe, and that Loki brother, he's as slick as Salavex.

01:10:11.920 --> 01:10:12.925
You know what I mean, trooper?

01:10:13.187 --> 01:10:15.720
In fact, me and my boys have started a Thor fan club.

01:10:16.547 --> 01:10:17.538
You know what I'm rapping?

01:10:17.841 --> 01:10:19.196
We're on your vibe, man.

01:10:19.881 --> 01:10:20.989
Hey, a Thor fan club.

01:10:21.009 --> 01:10:22.500
This pleases Thor very much.

01:10:22.962 --> 01:10:25.520
I shall speak of myself in the third person from now on.

01:10:25.941 --> 01:10:30.138
Uh, uh, yeah, I wasn't really into school all that much, but I hear you, Thor.

01:10:30.720 --> 01:10:33.077
So, so anyway, we had this fan club, right?

01:10:33.720 --> 01:10:36.480
And instead of naming it something like the Vice Lords of Valhalla,

01:10:36.720 --> 01:10:41.018
we gave it, like, a modern name, keeping things firmly in the 80s, you know?

01:10:41.720 --> 01:10:42.145
The Bloods.

01:10:42.671 --> 01:10:43.520
Ain't that off the wall, man?

01:10:44.123 --> 01:10:46.137
We follow your teachings to the letter, sir.

01:10:46.560 --> 01:10:50.300
Especially how you go around smiting fools with that wild, mad hammer of yours

01:10:50.883 --> 01:10:53.300
and getting people to know exactly what time it is, you hear?

01:10:53.965 --> 01:10:54.976
Have you a magic hammer?

01:10:55.620 --> 01:11:00.300
Nah, T. We don't have any Odin types around here to strap us with super fly hardware like yours,

01:11:00.982 --> 01:11:05.300
but we do have Mach 10s, Tech 9s, Tray 8s, Street Sweepers, and all that.

01:11:05.742 --> 01:11:07.320
Are you still on my vibe, brother?

01:11:07.841 --> 01:11:09.147
Hey, I like the sound of this.

01:11:09.468 --> 01:11:10.854
Me thinks I want to join your group.

01:11:11.115 --> 01:11:12.179
Do you pillage proper?

01:11:12.580 --> 01:11:13.183
Hell, yeah.

01:11:13.485 --> 01:11:14.732
We do it like a Viking.

01:11:14.953 --> 01:11:16.300
You oughta come party with us.

01:11:16.481 --> 01:11:18.173
We'll even make you an honorary Blood.

01:11:18.596 --> 01:11:18.858
Word.

01:11:19.320 --> 01:11:20.788
Ah, indiscriminate pillaging.

01:11:20.949 --> 01:11:23.100
This is, as we say, the school of old.

01:11:23.421 --> 01:11:25.120
When I am done with the wench, we shall meet.

01:11:25.601 --> 01:11:30.080
Till then, beware the frost giant, T.J., and the serpent with two tongues.

01:11:30.644 --> 01:11:32.120
Uh, yeah, okay, whatever.

01:11:32.501 --> 01:11:36.120
Yo, brother, where'd you land that funky, fresh, silver helmet of yours?

01:11:36.864 --> 01:11:39.120
Those wings on the side are wicked, money!

01:11:39.482 --> 01:11:40.918
Stop calling me a wench!

01:11:41.320 --> 01:11:43.589
I have much to say, if you would listen.

01:11:44.112 --> 01:11:46.100
For many centuries, people have asked questions.

01:11:46.461 --> 01:11:49.120
Why is my fatted calf gone after the gypsy woman appeared?

01:11:49.785 --> 01:11:51.120
Are there trolls living in my chimney?

01:11:52.023 --> 01:11:55.738
Aye, sure, I could tell ye the story of the twelve children on a platter,

01:11:56.320 --> 01:11:59.120
or the midsummer snow, and the spirit hatched from a cock's egg.

01:11:59.601 --> 01:12:01.891
But in the end, Amy, you need a spirit journey.

01:12:02.112 --> 01:12:04.120
A wandering spirit demands a wandering body.

01:12:04.400 --> 01:12:05.124
Take a long boat.

01:12:05.386 --> 01:12:06.532
Pack only what you can carry.

01:12:06.853 --> 01:12:08.120
Head toward the moon at high tide.

01:12:08.822 --> 01:12:10.067
Okay, thanks for the advice.

01:12:10.128 --> 01:12:12.879
And with that revelation, I'm going to have to change topics.

01:12:13.320 --> 01:12:14.776
That was Thor, Viking warrior.

01:12:15.120 --> 01:12:16.950
Coming up next, we have another guest.

01:12:17.131 --> 01:12:18.498
We'll be back right after this.

01:12:19.120 --> 01:12:21.920
How do you like to enjoy a Rusty Brown's Ring Donut?

01:12:22.502 --> 01:12:26.920
I like to lick lovingly around the outside and then thrust my tongue in the middle.

01:12:27.464 --> 01:12:28.920
I like to munch it vigorously.

01:12:30.005 --> 01:12:32.920
I just love the batter all over my face.

01:12:33.702 --> 01:12:37.820
On Friday nights, I just can't stop eating Rusty Brown's Ring Donuts.

01:12:38.402 --> 01:12:40.839
Oh my God, it's so good.

01:12:41.140 --> 01:12:43.920
Sometimes I like to wear women's panties and walk around Fifth Street.

01:12:45.064 --> 01:12:49.580
When you go downtown, make sure you enjoy Rusty Brown's Ring Donuts.

01:12:50.521 --> 01:12:58.720
Hi, I'm Jeremy Robar, entrepreneur, VIP, and founder of the revolutionary program Think Your Way to Success.

01:12:59.121 --> 01:13:03.640
It's a three-step program that's been changing lives and my income for the last two years.

01:13:03.920 --> 01:13:06.196
Five years ago, I was a nobody, just like you.

01:13:06.920 --> 01:13:13.399
After my Think Your Way to Success program, I spend the entire weekend in my jacuzzi, or engaging in the exciting sport of domino toppling.

01:13:13.720 --> 01:13:15.734
Hey, if you can think it, you can do it.

01:13:16.760 --> 01:13:19.218
One of my award-winning courses is sure to be perfect for you.

01:13:19.720 --> 01:13:24.138
The first course I call Think, Hold That Thought Complete, because that's what you do.

01:13:24.720 --> 01:13:28.520
Step two is known as Learn, Start Doing, where I explain the mysteries of starting.

01:13:28.961 --> 01:13:32.259
Or take the new accelerated course that will have you laughing and hugging strangers.

01:13:32.720 --> 01:13:34.815
Motivate, demonstrate, then motivate again.

01:13:35.720 --> 01:13:38.471
Just listen to these endorsements, and remember, these people volunteered.

01:13:38.552 --> 01:13:39.656
They aren't being paid much.

01:13:40.720 --> 01:13:42.614
I've been on the Think, Hold That Thought Complete program,

01:13:43.661 --> 01:13:47.199
and like I say, I'm finally going to start my career in being a well-paid, rich person.

